    <description>The Solar Wind Experiment (ESP) consisted of two sensors - one for electrons and one for positive ions. Each sensor consisted of a fan-shaped collimator, a 270 deg spherical electrostatic analyzer, and a micro-channel plate detector with five discrete anodes. The collimator field of view was 5 deg in azimuth and 60 deg in polar angle, the latter centered on the ecliptic plane (perpendicular to the spaceccraft spin axis). The experiment had four energy scanning modes, with an overall energy range of 30 eV to about 15.8 keV.</description>
